  "_comment": "Mapping comparison + 3C miss breakdown in a single demo. Four caches share one trace: 4-line DIRECT, 4-line 2-WAY set-associative, 4-line FULLY-associative, and 8-line FULLY-associative. The trace runs in two phases: cycles 0-7 alternate addresses 0 and 4 (the classic conflict thrash), then cycles 8-15 widen the working set to 5 addresses (0,4,8,12,16) so capacity becomes the dominant bottleneck on the 4-line fully-associative cache. Open Pipeline panel CACHE (LIVE): the direct cache thrashes from cycle 1 (all CONFLICT misses); the 2-way cache stays warm through cycle 5 (both 0 and 4 fit into set 0) but starts thrashing once 5 addresses cycle through; FULLY-4 is bottlenecked by CAPACITY; FULLY-8 only sees COMPULSORY cold-start misses.",
